<date box="[1309,1402,152,176]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" value="1930-08">
VIII. 
<number box="[1372,1402,152,176]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" value="30.0">30</number>
</date>
, S. Issiki. One antenna, one wing, one leg and abdomen including hypopygium are mounted on a similarly labeled microscope slide. The remaining five legs are still attached to the body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
